title: Katie Sandwina With the Anvil
description: Katie Sandwina, also known as a Strong Lady, on a bed of nails. Two men are getting ready to strike the anvil situated atop her abdomen with hammers. Ringling Museum Archives.
subject: Infliction of pain

title: The Stone, the Hammer & Billy Wells
description: Billy Wells whose skull was thick, he allowed stone to be laid on top his head and broken with a hammer. Barnum and Bailey Attraction. Ringling Museum Archives.
subject: Infliction of pain

title: Drawing of Suspended Man
description: Drawing of a man suspended in air by his chest. Two men in the background are seen pulling ropes connected to a tree branch.
subject: Infliction of pain

title: Maid of Steel the First
creator: Bernard Kobel
description: Woman lying on a bed of nails. Her arms are suspended by behind her back. She is known as the Maid of Steel. Photographed by Bernard Kobel.
subject: Needles and nails

title: Posing for Tattoos
description: Woman posing for photograph while being tattooed. Her tattoo artist is focusing solely on her arm, while she is facing the camera. Ringling Museum Archives.
subject: Needles and nails

title: The Human Pincushion
description: Ringling Museum Archives.Arthur Plumhoff, his nerves did not register pain at all and he stuck these numerous pins through his cheeks without feeling. Believe It Or Not Shows, Chicago Worlds Fair 1933. Ringling Museum Archives.
subject: Needles and nails

title: Captain Ringman Jack
description: Captain Ringman Jack pictured lifting a large, canon-ball sized weight by his chest. Ringling Museum Archives.
subject: Strength

title: Charmion, the Strong Lady
creator: Frederick Whitman Glasier
description: Lavarie Vallee, known by her stage name as Charmion, bares her flesh and flexes for photographer Frederick Whitman Glasier. Her remarkable muscles dominate the frame, centered and molded by bright light and dark shadows against a stark black background. Her extraordinary physical ability is inseperably characterized parallel to her femininity and sexuality. Ringling Museum Archives.
subject: Strength

title: The Great and Beautiful Katie Sandwina
creator: Frederick Whitman Glasier
description: Barnum and Bailey Circus' Katie Sandwina, when she is not pinned down to a bed of nails by a large anvil and enduring a beating with hammers, poses before photographer Frederick Whitman Glasier as a muscular ballerina. She wears flowers, feathers, and a sequined leotard. Ringling Museum Archives.
subject: Strength

title: The Iron Tongue
description: Sisto, the Iron Tongue man, lifts heavy weights with his tongue and is shown here lifting a piece of steel with his muscular tongue. Ringling Museum Archives.
subject: Strength

title: Maid of Steel the Second
description: Companion photograph to  Maid of Steel the First, she is pictured here on a set of five knives. A chain stretches from her waist to her ankles, keeping her in this precarious position. Ringling Museum Archives.
subject: Swords

title: Sharp Footed
description: Rosita Reverdy stands on a ladder with rungs of swords. She is barefoot, balancing on the blade of one sword. Ringing Museum Archives.
subject: Swords

title: Long Way Down
description: Louise Long, is pictured here swallowing a pair of scissors. She was a performer with the Ringling Bros & Barnum and Bailey Circus. Ringling Museum Archives.
subject: Swords

title: If the Sword Fits, Swallow It (Or Three)
description: Alex Linton is seen here swallowing four large swords. He was a performer with the Sells-Floto Circus. Ringling Museum Archives.
subject: Swords

title: The Sword and the Strange
description: A sword swallower performing in the King Bros. Circus Sideshow. He is standing on a platform in front of a banner stating "Strange People In All Parts".
subject: Swords

title: Trapeze Disrobing Act (Thomas Edison 1901)
creator: Thomas Edison
description: Film shot by Thomas Edison circa 1901, featuring famous aerialist Laverie Vallee, better-known by her stage name of Charmion
subject: Strength
